# NCAAF-P1.2 artifacts.
#
# The posterior parquet is a MODEL OUTPUT, not source: it is ~1.7 MB, it is regenerated by
# `run_team_strength.py` on every run, and its durable home is the lake
# (`s3://credence-sports-lakehouse/ncaaf/derived/team_strength_week/`), which is what the
# `ncaaf_team_strength_week` dbt model actually reads. Committing it would version a binary
# that is guaranteed to drift from the lake copy the moment anyone re-runs.
#
# The two small diagnostics ARE committed on purpose — they are the fit's audit trail
# (per-season variance components, home-field advantage, covariate coefficients, gate
# results) and reviewing a model change means reading exactly those.
*.parquet
